race.comment: Tough. COATACHINO (9) was back on track when narrowly beaten here over 1500m for the new yard, and then raced favourite in a similar contest and didn't finish it off. Is thrown in with the 4kg claim and deserves another chance. ROUNDABOUT GLORY (1) needed the outing here first-up and then led and was swamped at Belmont over 1300m. He's better suited at 1600m and has an inside barrier and a handy 2kg. PETITE VITESSE (2) did a good job missing 2.4L at Northam first-up over 1300m and then raced an equal favourite over the same trip at Esperance and settled at the back of the field and was unable to make up the ground. Has a handy 3kg claim, and the step up to a mile should suit this time around. MISTER POPCORN (3) will give away a start, but he finished the race off well first up over 1500m, having his first go for the new barn. May need longer now, but he can come late.
